data.title: Amazing burgers
data.text: First time in and the food and service was amazing and quick. Price is write about what you would pay at any fast food place

data.title: World Class Hamburgers and Fries
data.text: Five Guys is a fast food chain that has won a pile of awards for focusing on doing hamburgers and fries the right way.  All burgers are made from fresh ground beef that has never been frozen. The burgers are fried on a flat top grill.   The fries are hand cut from the giant bags of  russet potatoes strategically piled in locations around the isles.  Enjoy the free peanuts in the shell while waiting for your order.

data.title: Fast, friendly, tasty
data.text: Was in the mood for a good burger, so we stopped in and enjoyed a great cheeseburger and fries with the some friends and my kiddos couldn't wolf it down fast enough. Cooked perfectly, hardly any grease, and deliciously seasoned fries...can't wait to go back!

data.title: Quick bite
data.text:
We came here for a quick bite.  The food was good.  They do offer free unshelled peanuts which you can scoop out in case you have a peanut allergy.

The food costs a little more than your other fast food burger joints but these burgers and fries are better. 

This location was clean and the staff were friendly which is nice to see as well.

data.title: Giving it a try
data.text: The food was ok. Not anything that made us want to hurry back and get again. Prices are quite expensive as each item is paid for individually. It was very clean and the staff was friendly. Should at least try it just to see what it's all about :)

data.title: Good burger
data.text: The employees seemed happy to be there and I enjoyed that! I really loved the cheese burger that I had! It melted in my mouth! The only down side of this visit was the presentation of my food, in the sense of my fries. They were poured on top of my burger and was a mess to grab but other than that, I enjoyed myself!

data.title: Late lunch
data.text: Cashier was very friendly. Stated this location offers milkshakes and can add bacon to the shakes. Thought this was a neat option. We ate our faves and was not  disappointed.

data.title: Great place for a burger and fries!
data.text: Great food and prompt service. This place is always busy. They give you a good portion for what you order, so bring your appetite!

data.title: Typical but good five guys
data.text: This was a good lunch. Nothing out of the ordinary from any five guys. Portions were plenty. Food was hot and good. Fries and burger. Can't complain!

data.title: family visit
data.text: This was my family's first visit to Five Guys.  The burgers were great.  The fries were a little soggy.  The little burger would be enough for many people.  The regular burger comes with 2 patties.  It is a little expensive.

data.title: good
data.text: quick service friendly fries great burger just ok had better at 5 guys but we we were  tired hungry and it was 98  and there was no air conditioning in there I felt so sorry for the employees we took our meal back to our room

data.title: Nice Place
data.text: Both my granddaughter and I ordered a regular hamburger with fries.  Hamburger was fine but Culvers has much better fries.  The fries served here had burnt edges.  Service and cleanliness were fine.

data.title: Deliciousness
data.text: I was doing some shopping and stopped at this five guys and grab cheeseburger fries and a banana shake and it was awesome. The burger was really good and it wasnt dry at all. The best part of my meal was the shake it was absolutely delicious using real fruit with shakes makes a big difference and it was worth it.

data.title: Consistant
data.text: Looking for a place to eat and came across this 5 Guys.  Have eaten in many and this location was consistent with the other restaurants.  Food was good and service was very friendly.

data.title: One of the best Burgers we've ever had
data.text: Five Guys truly has great burgers. They have 2 locations in Sioux Falls. Minnesota Ave and Louise Ave are the 2 locations. Want an appetizer... how about some peanuts to start out. Order up at the counter for one of a kind burgers-- burgers have many add ones that you can make them one of a kind. How about a hand spun shake? We recommend the Salted Caramel and the Strawberry Shakes. Ooo, so good.  Between the 2 of us we split a large fry. The burgers are large enough and filling but if you are looking for a little extra, you can add patties. One of your favorite restaurants for sure! For the two of us we spent $26-- burgers (1 patty & 2 patties), 2 shakes and a large fry to split)

data.title: Love this place
data.text: Burgers made to order with whatever toppings you wish. Fresh ingredients. Large servings of fries cut in-house. Cajun were good, but may just stick to the original next time. Fast and friendly.

data.title: Never again.
data.text: When my simple order for a family of four came to over 40 dollars, I said to myself that these had better be the best burgers that I've ever had.  They weren't.  They were very standard, very overpriced burgers and fries.  We could have had a nice sit-down meal in a quiet place for that kind of money, but instead we got four middle-of-the-road burgers in a room that had the decibel level of a frat house party.  I would absolutely consider a microwave burger from a gas station next time instead of five guys if those were my two choices.

data.title: Nothing great
data.text: We went there because we heard how good it was. Might try a different time to see if it is better. I thought the fries were just ok not the rave that I had heard. There were a lot of them

data.title: Surprised by quality
data.text: A bit expensive for fast food - $20 for two people (2 burgers, split reg fry, 2 drinks). However, friendly service and the burgers were better than expected - not your typical round frozen patty. Fries were good - didn't taste or appear very greasy as others have commented. Loud atmosphere, bit untidy in dining area and bathrooms. Would still rather dine here than a Burger King or McDonalds.

data.title: Need a burger go here
data.text: Man I needed a burger and this was GOOD went for lunch and it was really good did not want to leave till all my fries were gone, yummm
